# PDF Merger Development Rules

## UI/UX Standards
- **Premium Aesthetics**: Always adhere to the HSL-based design system and glassmorphism.
- **Micro-animations**: Use `framer-motion` for all state transitions (list removals, reordering, status messages).
- **Responsive**: Ensure the layout works seamlessly on mobile and desktop.

## Technical Standards
- **Client-Side Only**: Never send PDF data to a server. All manipulation must happen in the browser using `pdf-lib`.
- **Error Handling**: Provide clear, user-friendly error messages for invalid files or failed merges.
- **Performance**: Use `Web Workers` if merging becomes a performance bottleneck for very large files.

## Workflow
- Before any change to the PDF logic, run the `/validate-pdf` workflow.
- Maintain the `README.md` with up-to-date Node.js and Vite instructions.
